7:
Doesn't look like anyone's coming to my
rescue anytime soon... Sticking around
here isn't gonna do me any good.
11:
Wait, that's right! The Crimson Blades
gave me something for this.
26:
I'm sure glad both navy and pirate ships
use the same SOS signal.
30:
Oh, I've yet to introduce myself. I'm Rain,
a cadet in the Gaea Royal Navy.
32:
And that certainly was fortunate.
The red signal, yes?
A request for backup fire.
42:
Oh, was it? Oh, dear. I might have to
take another makeup exam...
45: Well, I suppose all's well that ends well.
55:
Indeed! I'll soon be graduating from
the academy, you see. This ship isn't
mine, but one assigned to me for field
experience.
59:
Wow, and they let you sail all the way
out here by yourself?
63:
Not exactly. I saw the signal and
thought someone needed help. I don't
think they'll be pleased about this.
68: A yellow one? Or was it green?
71:
Hard to tell. Some sort of yellow-green,
I think? Which means...
83: I'll do what I can to help!
87: Appreciate it! And sorry about this.
95: Alk, take care of the ship!
106:
Nice work out there, Rain! I've never
seen anyone run on the water like that
before.
109:
These shoes were designed by
the Royal Navy, but they're quite
difficult to use.
111:
I'm the only person able to use them.
It's because of that reason I was able
to enroll in the naval academy.
118:
O-oh, I wouldn't say it's anything that
special. Heh... I mean, I still have a long
ways to go.
123:
Yeah?
I take it you're still pretty young then?
126: I... I'm fifteen. Why do you ask?
129:
I thought you were someone older
at first, but you're still a kid, huh?
134:
I'll have you know that I am a navy
officer, and won't tolerate being treated
like a—
137: Also, your voice is getting higher.
141:
Sorry, I didn't mean to tease you!
Truth is, I'm impressed someone
as young as you are being this
accomplished.
143:
Not only that, you sailed that ship
by yourself and ran on water!
You're really something.
147:
Oh, I wouldn't...
It's nothing special, really...
152:
Actually, would you be interested in
enlisting in the Gaea Royal Navy
yourself?
156:
Even after being rescued, you offered to
help without a moment's hesitation.
That's seaworthy courage if I've ever
seen it!
161:
We're always looking for recruits! And
we could go busting pirates together!
173:
You're seriously gonna give me a heart
attack one of these days... Would you
stop falling into the sea already?!
176:
It's not like you have nine lives,
you know.
191:
Yeah... Sorry, Rain.
These pirates are actually—
197:
The Crimson Blades!
The pirate crew feared across all seas,
led by the one and only Captain Marina!
205:
As an aspiring sailor, I'll need to have
my finger on the pulse of the sea—
including pirates! I can't let this
opportunity go to waste!
208:
Please, allow me to join your crew!
I mean, we've already fought together
once, right?
213:
Yeesh... People here sure are intense.
Maybe it's something in the water.
